actions.comment:
Thanks for the feature request! `SKCanvas.WritePixels()` is indeed a real Skia C++ API (`SkCanvas::writePixels`) that hasn't been exposed in SkiaSharp yet — this is a valid gap.

In the meantime, you can avoid per-frame `SKImage` allocation by using `SKBitmap.InstallPixels` to wrap your existing pixel buffer and drawing that bitmap directly:

```csharp
// One-time setup — wrap your existing pixel buffer (must be pinned/unmanaged)
var bmp = new SKBitmap();
bmp.InstallPixels(imageInfo, pixelBufferPtr, imageInfo.RowBytes);

// Per-frame — no allocation, direct blit:
canvas.DrawBitmap(bmp, 0, 0);
```

This avoids creating a new `SKImage` each frame while the proper `WritePixels` API is added.
